SIMPLE: wiry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wiry
<hw>Wir"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>wiery</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Made of wire; like wire; drawn out like
wire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capable of endurance; tough; sinewy; <as>as, a
<ex>wiry</ex> frame or constitution</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A little
<xex>wiry</xex> sergeant of meek demeanor and strong sense.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He bore his age well, and seemed to retain a <qex>wiry</qex> vigor
and alertness.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wis</ent>⟦br⟧
